{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844112400,"sessionID":"ses_28772e49effe617laS4xnvcyTz","part":{"id":"prt_d788ea7500015BYzSouDMopu5O","messageID":"msg_d788de8990015OAgdLtehtCT7J","sessionID":"ses_28772e49effe617laS4xnvcyTz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0e57ceca9d2a460690614ebf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package handler\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"net/http\"\n5: \n6: \t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n7: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/unstructured\"\n8: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n9: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n10: \tcorev1lister \"k8s.io/client-go/listers/core/v1\"\n11: \n12: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/processor\"\n13: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/response\"\n14: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types\"\n15: )\n16: \n17: type SandboxHandler struct {\n18: \tdynamicClient dynamic.Interface\n19: \tk8sClient     kubernetes.Interface\n20: \tpodLister     corev1lister.PodLister\n21: \tarLister      processor.AgentRuntimeLister\n22: \tciLister      processor.CodeInterpreterLister\n23: \tnamespace     string\n24: }\n25: \n26: func NewSandboxHandler(\n27: \tdynamicClient dynamic.Interface,\n28: \tk8sClient kubernetes.Interface,\n29: \tpodLister corev1lister.PodLister,\n30: \tarLister processor.AgentRuntimeLister,\n31: \tciLister processor.CodeInterpreterLister,\n32: \tnamespace string,\n33: ) *SandboxHandler {\n34: \treturn &SandboxHandler{\n35: \t\tdynamicClient: dynamicClient,\n36: \t\tk8sClient:     k8sClient,\n37: \t\tpodLister:     podLister,\n38: \t\tarLister:      arLister,\n39: \t\tciLister:      ciLister,\n40: \t\tnamespace:     namespace,\n41: \t}\n42: }\n43: \n44: func (h *SandboxHandler) HandleAgentRuntimeCreate(c *gin.Context) {\n45: \tvar req types.CreateSandboxRequest\n46: \tif err := c.ShouldBindJSON(&req); err != nil {\n47: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusBadRequest, 40002, \"Invalid request body\")\n48: \t\treturn\n49: \t}\n50: \n51: \tif err := req.Validate(); err != nil {\n52: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusBadRequest, 40003, err.Error())\n53: \t\treturn\n54: \t}\n55: \n56: \treq.Kind = \"AgentRuntime\"\n57: \n58: \truntime, err := processor.GetAgentRuntime(h.arLister, req.Namespace, req.Name)\n59: \tif err != nil {\n60: \t\tif err == processor.ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound {\n61: \t\t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusNotFound, 40401, \"agent runtime not found\")\n62: \t\t\treturn\n63: \t\t}\n64: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n65: \t\treturn\n66: \t}\n67: \n68: \tproc := processor.NewSandboxProcessor(h.dynamicClient, h.k8sClient, h.podLister, h.arLister, h.ciLister, h.namespace)\n69: \n70: \tsessionID, err := proc.GenerateSessionID()\n71: \tif err != nil {\n72: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n73: \t\treturn\n74: \t}\n75: \n76: \tsandbox, err := proc.BuildSandboxObject(runtime, sessionID)\n77: \tif err != nil {\n78: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n79: \t\treturn\n80: \t}\n81: \n82: \tuserClient := h.dynamicClient.Resource(processor.SandboxGVR).Namespace(runtime.Namespace)\n83: \n84: \tinfo, err := proc.CreateSandbox(c.Request.Context(), sandbox, false, userClient, sessionID)\n85: \tif err != nil {\n86: \t\tif err == processor.ErrSandboxCreationTimeout {\n87: \t\t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n88: \t\t\treturn\n89: \t\t}\n90: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n91: \t\treturn\n92: \t}\n93: \n94: \tresp := types.CreateSandboxResponse{\n95: \t\tSessionID:   info.SessionID,\n96: \t\tSandboxID:   info.SandboxID,\n97: \t\tSandboxName: info.SandboxName,\n98: \t\tEntryPoints: info.EntryPoints,\n99: \t}\n100: \n101: \tresponse.JSON(c, http.StatusOK, resp)\n102: }\n103: \n104: func (h *SandboxHandler) HandleCodeInterpreterCreate(c *gin.Context) {\n105: \tvar req types.CreateSandboxRequest\n106: \tif err := c.ShouldBindJSON(&req); err != nil {\n107: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusBadRequest, 40002, \"Invalid request body\")\n108: \t\treturn\n109: \t}\n110: \n111: \tif err := req.Validate(); err != nil {\n112: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusBadRequest, 40003, err.Error())\n113: \t\treturn\n114: \t}\n115: \n116: \treq.Kind = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n117: \n118: \tinterpreter, err := processor.GetCodeInterpreter(h.ciLister, req.Namespace, req.Name)\n119: \tif err != nil {\n120: \t\tif err == processor.ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound {\n121: \t\t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusNotFound, 40401, \"code interpreter not found\")\n122: \t\t\treturn\n123: \t\t}\n124: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n125: \t\treturn\n126: \t}\n127: \n128: \tproc := processor.NewSandboxProcessor(h.dynamicClient, h.k8sClient, h.podLister, h.arLister, h.ciLister, h.namespace)\n129: \n130: \tsessionID, err := proc.GenerateSessionID()\n131: \tif err != nil {\n132: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n133: \t\treturn\n134: \t}\n135: \n136: \tvar sandbox *unstructured.Unstructured\n137: \tisWarmPool := false\n138: \n139: \tsandbox, err = proc.BuildCodeInterpreterSandbox(interpreter, sessionID)\n140: \tif err != nil {\n141: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n142: \t\treturn\n143: \t}\n144: \n145: \tuserClient := h.dynamicClient.Resource(processor.SandboxGVR).Namespace(interpreter.Namespace)\n146: \n147: \tinfo, err := proc.CreateSandbox(c.Request.Context(), sandbox, isWarmPool, userClient, sessionID)\n148: \tif err != nil {\n149: \t\tif err == processor.ErrSandboxCreationTimeout {\n150: \t\t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n151: \t\t\treturn\n152: \t\t}\n153: \t\tresponse.Error(c, http.StatusInternalServerError, 50002, \"internal server error\")\n154: \t\treturn\n155: \t}\n156: \n157: \tresp := types.CreateSandboxResponse{\n158: \t\tSessionID:   info.SessionID,\n159: \t\tSandboxID:   info.SandboxID,\n160: \t\tSandboxName: info.SandboxName,\n161: \t\tEntryPoints: info.EntryPoints,\n162: \t}\n163: \n164: \tresponse.JSON(c, http.StatusOK, resp)\n165: }\n\n(End of file - total 165 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package handler\n\nimport (\n\t\"net/http\"\n\n\t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/unstructured\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n\tcorev1lister \"k8s.io/client-go/listers/core/v1\"\n\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/processor\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/response\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types\"\n)\n\ntype SandboxHandler struct {\n\tdynamicClient dynamic.Interface\n\tk8sClient     kubernetes.Interface\n\tpodLister     corev1lister.PodLister","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox.go","time":{"start":1775844112379,"end":1775844112399}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844112402,"sessionID":"ses_28772e49effe617laS4xnvcyTz","part":{"id":"prt_d788eaca4001bNjzkXgSs4KGjv","messageID":"msg_d788de8990015OAgdLtehtCT7J","sessionID":"ses_28772e49effe617laS4xnvcyTz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b4e5e254fb1c4fb180f8182b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_processor.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_processor.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package processor\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"crypto/rand\"\n6: \t\"fmt\"\n7: \t\"math/big\"\n8: \t\"net\"\n9: \t\"strings\"\n10: \t\"time\"\n11: \n12: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n13: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n14: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/unstructured\"\n15: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/labels\"\n16: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n17: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n18: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n19: \tcorev1lister \"k8s.io/client-go/listers/core/v1\"\n20: \n21: \truntimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n22: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types\"\n23: )\n24: \n25: var (\n26: \tSandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n27: \t\tGroup:    \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n28: \t\tVersion:  \"v1alpha1\",\n29: \t\tResource: \"sandboxes\",\n30: \t}\n31: \n32: \tSandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n33: \t\tGroup:    \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\",\n34: \t\tVersion:  \"v1alpha1\",\n35: \t\tResource: \"sandboxclaims\",\n36: \t}\n37: )\n38: \n39: const (\n40: \tSessionIDLabelKey        = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"\n41: \tIdleTimeoutAnnotation    = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"\n42: \tSandboxNameLabelKey      = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"\n43: \tSandboxPodNameAnnotation = \"agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name\"\n44: )\n45: \n46: var (\n47: \tErrAgentRuntimeNotFound    = fmt.Errorf(\"agent runtime not found\")\n48: \tErrCodeInterpreterNotFound = fmt.Errorf(\"code interpreter not found\")\n49: \tErrTemplateMissing         = fmt.Errorf(\"template is missing\")\n50: \tErrSandboxCreationTimeout  = fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox creation timeout\")\n51: )\n52: \n53: type AgentRuntimeLister interface {\n54: \tAgentRuntimes(namespace string) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n55: }\n56: \n57: type AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister interface {\n58: \tGet(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n59: }\n60: \n61: type CodeInterpreterLister interface {\n62: \tCodeInterpreters(namespace string) CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister\n63: }\n64: \n65: type CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister interface {\n66: \tGet(name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n67: }\n68: \n69: type SandboxProcessor struct {\n70: \tdynamicClient dynamic.Interface\n71: \tk8sClient     kubernetes.Interface\n72: \tpodLister     corev1lister.PodLister\n73: \tarLister      AgentRuntimeLister\n74: \tciLister      CodeInterpreterLister\n75: \tnamespace     string\n76: }\n77: \n78: func NewSandboxProcessor(\n79: \tdynamicClient dynamic.Interface,\n80: \tk8sClient kubernetes.Interface,\n81: \tpodLister corev1lister.PodLister,\n82: \tarLister AgentRuntimeLister,\n83: \tciLister CodeInterpreterLister,\n84: \tnamespace string,\n85: ) *SandboxProcessor {\n86: \treturn &SandboxProcessor{\n87: \t\tdynamicClient: dynamicClient,\n88: \t\tk8sClient:     k8sClient,\n89: \t\tpodLister:     podLister,\n90: \t\tarLister:      arLister,\n91: \t\tciLister:      ciLister,\n92: \t\tnamespace:     namespace,\n93: \t}\n94: }\n95: \n96: func RandString(n int) (string, error) {\n97: \tconst letters = \"abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz\"\n98: \tresult := make([]byte, n)\n99: \tfor i := 0; i < n; i++ {\n100: \t\tnum, err := rand.Int(rand.Reader, big.NewInt(int64(len(letters))))\n101: \t\tif err != nil {\n102: \t\t\treturn \"\", err\n103: \t\t}\n104: \t\tresult[i] = letters[num.Int64()]\n105: \t}\n106: \treturn string(result), nil\n107: }\n108: \n109: func (p *SandboxProcessor) GenerateSessionID() (string, error) {\n110: \tid, err := rand.Int(rand.Reader, big.NewInt(1e18))\n111: \tif err != nil {\n112: \t\treturn \"\", err\n113: \t}\n114: \treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%018d\", id.Int64()), nil\n115: }\n116: \n117: func GetAgentRuntime(lister AgentRuntimeLister, namespace, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error) {\n118: \tif lister == nil {\n119: \t\treturn nil, ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound\n120: \t}\n121: \tar, err := lister.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(name)\n122: \tif err != nil {\n123: \t\treturn nil, ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound\n124: \t}\n125: \treturn ar, nil\n126: }\n127: \n128: func GetCodeInterpreter(lister CodeInterpreterLister, namespace, name string) (*runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) {\n129: \tif lister == nil {\n130: \t\treturn nil, ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound\n131: \t}\n132: \tci, err := lister.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(name)\n133: \tif err != nil {\n134: \t\treturn nil, ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound\n135: \t}\n136: \treturn ci, nil\n137: }\n138: \n139: func (p *SandboxProcessor) BuildSandboxObject(runtime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error) {\n140: \tsuffix, err := RandString(8)\n141: \tif err != nil {\n142: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to generate random suffix: %w\", err)\n143: \t}\n144: \n145: \tsandboxName := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s\", runtime.Name, suffix)\n146: \n147: \tlabels := map[string]string{}\n148: \tfor k, v := range runtime.Labels {\n149: \t\tlabels[k] = v\n150: \t}\n151: \tlabels[SessionIDLabelKey] = sessionID\n152: \n153: \tannotations := map[string]string{}\n154: \tfor k, v := range runtime.Annotations {\n155: \t\tannotations[k] = v\n156: \t}\n157: \n158: \tnow := time.Now()\n159: \tshutdownTime := now.Add(8 * time.Hour)\n160: \n161: \tcontainer := map[string]interface{}{\n162: \t\t\"name\":  \"agent-runtime\",\n163: \t\t\"image\": runtime.Spec.Container.Image,\n164: \t}\n165: \n166: \tif len(runtime.Spec.Container.Command) > 0 {\n167: \t\tcontainer[\"command\"] = runtime.Spec.Container.Command\n168: \t}\n169: \n170: \tif len(runtime.Spec.Container.Args) > 0 {\n171: \t\tcontainer[\"args\"] = runtime.Spec.Container.Args\n172: \t}\n173: \n174: \tif len(runtime.Spec.Container.Env) > 0 {\n175: \t\tenvBytes := make([]interface{}, len(runtime.Spec.Container.Env))\n176: \t\tfor i, envVar := range runtime.Spec.Container.Env {\n177: \t\t\tenvMap := map[string]interface{}{\"name\": envVar.Name}\n178: \t\t\tif envVar.Value != \"\" {\n179: \t\t\t\tenvMap[\"value\"] = envVar.Value\n180: \t\t\t}\n181: \t\t\tif envVar.ValueFrom != nil {\n182: \t\t\t\tvalueFromMap := map[string]interface{}{}\n183: \t\t\t\tif envVar.ValueFrom.ConfigMapKeyRef != nil {\n184: \t\t\t\t\tvalueFromMap[\"configMapKeyRef\"] = map[string]interface{}{\n185: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"name\": envVar.ValueFrom.ConfigMapKeyRef.Name,\n186: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"key\":  envVar.ValueFrom.ConfigMapKeyRef.Key,\n187: \t\t\t\t\t}\n188: \t\t\t\t}\n189: \t\t\t\tif envVar.ValueFrom.SecretKeyRef != nil {\n190: \t\t\t\t\tvalueFromMap[\"secretKeyRef\"] = map[string]interface{}{\n191: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"name\": envVar.ValueFrom.SecretKeyRef.Name,\n192: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"key\":  envVar.ValueFrom.SecretKeyRef.Key,\n193: \t\t\t\t\t}\n194: \t\t\t\t}\n195: \t\t\t\tif envVar.ValueFrom.ResourceFieldRef != nil {\n196: \t\t\t\t\tvalueFromMap[\"resourceFieldRef\"] = map[string]interface{}{\n197: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"resource\":      envVar.ValueFrom.ResourceFieldRef.Resource,\n198: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"containerName\": envVar.ValueFrom.ResourceFieldRef.ContainerName,\n199: \t\t\t\t\t}\n200: \t\t\t\t}\n201: \t\t\t\tif envVar.ValueFrom.FieldRef != nil {\n202: \t\t\t\t\tvalueFromMap[\"fieldRef\"] = map[string]interface{}{\n203: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"fieldPath\": envVar.ValueFrom.FieldRef.FieldPath,\n204: \t\t\t\t\t}\n205: \t\t\t\t}\n206: \t\t\t\tenvMap[\"valueFrom\"] = valueFromMap\n207: \t\t\t}\n208: \t\t\tenvBytes[i] = envMap\n209: \t\t}\n210: \t\tcontainer[\"env\"] = envBytes\n211: \t}\n212: \n213: \tsandbox := &unstructured.Unstructured{\n214: \t\tObject: map[string]interface{}{\n215: \t\t\t\"apiVersion\": \"agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1\",\n216: \t\t\t\"kind\":       \"Sandbox\",\n217: \t\t\t\"metadata\": map[string]interface{}{\n218: \t\t\t\t\"name\":        sandboxName,\n219: \t\t\t\t\"namespace\":   runtime.Namespace,\n220: \t\t\t\t\"labels\":      labels,\n221: \t\t\t\t\"annotations\": annotations,\n222: \t\t\t},\n223: \t\t\t\"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n224: \t\t\t\t\"podTemplate\": map[string]interface{}{\n225: \t\t\t\t\t\"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n226: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"containers\": []interface{}{container},\n227: \t\t\t\t\t},\n228: \t\t\t\t},\n229: \t\t\t},\n230: \t\t\t\"lifecycle\": map[string]interface{}{\n231: \t\t\t\t\"shutdownTime\": shutdownTime.Format(time.RFC3339),\n232: \t\t\t},\n233: \t\t},\n234: \t}\n235: \n236: \treturn sandbox, nil\n237: }\n238: \n239: func (p *SandboxProcessor) BuildSandboxClaimObject(interpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error) {\n240: \tsuffix, err := RandString(8)\n241: \tif err != nil {\n242: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to generate random suffix: %w\", err)\n243: \t}\n244: \n245: \tclaimName := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-claim-%s\", interpreter.Name, suffix)\n246: \n247: \tlabels := map[string]string{}\n248: \tfor k, v := range interpreter.Labels {\n249: \t\tlabels[k] = v\n250: \t}\n251: \tlabels[SessionIDLabelKey] = sessionID\n252: \n253: \tclaim := &unstructured.Unstructured{\n254: \t\tObject: map[string]interface{}{\n255: \t\t\t\"apiVersion\": \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1\",\n256: \t\t\t\"kind\":       \"SandboxClaim\",\n257: \t\t\t\"metadata\": map[string]interface{}{\n258: \t\t\t\t\"name\":      claimName,\n259: \t\t\t\t\"namespace\": interpreter.Namespace,\n260: \t\t\t\t\"labels\":    labels,\n261: \t\t\t},\n262: \t\t\t\"spec\": map[string]interface{}{},\n263: \t\t},\n264: \t}\n265: \n266: \treturn claim, nil\n267: }\n268: \n269: func (p *SandboxProcessor) BuildCodeInterpreterSandbox(interpreter *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, sessionID string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error) {\n270: \tsuffix, err := RandString(8)\n271: \tif err != nil {\n272: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to generate random suffix: %w\", err)\n273: \t}\n274: \n275: \tsandboxName := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s-%s\", interpreter.Name, suffix)\n276: \n277: \tlabels := map[string]string{}\n278: \tfor k, v := range interpreter.Labels {\n279: \t\tlabels[k] = v\n280: \t}\n281: \tlabels[SessionIDLabelKey] = sessionID\n282: \n283: \tannotations := map[string]string{}\n284: \tfor k, v := range interpreter.Annotations {\n285: \t\tannotations[k] = v\n286: \t}\n287: \n288: \tnow := time.Now()\n289: \tshutdownTime := now.Add(8 * time.Hour)\n290: \n291: \tsandbox := &unstructured.Unstructured{\n292: \t\tObject: map[string]interface{}{\n293: \t\t\t\"apiVersion\": \"agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1\",\n294: \t\t\t\"kind\":       \"Sandbox\",\n295: \t\t\t\"metadata\": map[string]interface{}{\n296: \t\t\t\t\"name\":        sandboxName,\n297: \t\t\t\t\"namespace\":   interpreter.Namespace,\n298: \t\t\t\t\"labels\":      labels,\n299: \t\t\t\t\"annotations\": annotations,\n300: \t\t\t},\n301: \t\t\t\"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n302: \t\t\t\t\"podTemplate\": map[string]interface{}{\n303: \t\t\t\t\t\"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n304: \t\t\t\t\t\t\"containers\": []interface{}{\n305: \t\t\t\t\t\t\tmap[string]interface{}{\n306: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\"name\":  \"code-interpreter\",\n307: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\"image\": interpreter.Spec.Image,\n308: \t\t\t\t\t\t\t},\n309: \t\t\t\t\t\t},\n310: \t\t\t\t\t},\n311: \t\t\t\t},\n312: \t\t\t},\n313: \t\t\t\"lifecycle\": map[string]interface{}{\n314: \t\t\t\t\"shutdownTime\": shutdownTime.Format(time.RFC3339),\n315: \t\t\t},\n316: \t\t},\n317: \t}\n318: \n319: \treturn sandbox, nil\n320: }\n321: \n322: func (p *SandboxProcessor) resolvePodIP(ctx context.Context, sandboxNamespace, sandboxName string) (string, error) {\n323: \tpodName := sandboxName\n324: \n325: \tpod, err := p.podLister.Pods(sandboxNamespace).Get(podName)\n326: \tif err == nil {\n327: \t\tif pod.Status.Phase != corev1.PodRunning {\n328: \t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"pod %s is not running (phase: %s)\", podName, pod.Status.Phase)\n329: \t\t}\n330: \t\tif pod.Status.PodIP == \"\" {\n331: \t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"pod %s has no IP assigned\", podName)\n332: \t\t}\n333: \t\treturn pod.Status.PodIP, nil\n334: \t}\n335: \n336: \tselector := labels.SelectorFromSet(labels.Set{\n337: \t\tSandboxNameLabelKey: sandboxName,\n338: \t})\n339: \n340: \tpodList, err := p.podLister.Pods(sandboxNamespace).List(selector)\n341: \tif err != nil {\n342: \t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list pods: %w\", err)\n343: \t}\n344: \n345: \tfor _, pod := range podList {\n346: \t\tfor _, ownerRef := range pod.OwnerReferences {\n347: \t\t\tif ownerRef.Kind == \"Sandbox\" && ownerRef.Name == sandboxName {\n348: \t\t\t\tif pod.Status.Phase != corev1.PodRunning {\n349: \t\t\t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"pod %s is not running (phase: %s)\", pod.Name, pod.Status.Phase)\n350: \t\t\t\t}\n351: \t\t\t\tif pod.Status.PodIP == \"\" {\n352: \t\t\t\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"pod %s has no IP assigned\", pod.Name)\n353: \t\t\t\t}\n354: \t\t\t\treturn pod.Status.PodIP, nil\n355: \t\t\t}\n356: \t\t}\n357: \t}\n358: \n359: \tfor _, pod := range podList {\n360: \t\tif pod.Status.Phase == corev1.PodRunning && pod.Status.PodIP != \"\" {\n361: \t\t\treturn pod.Status.PodIP, nil\n362: \t\t}\n363: \t}\n364: \n365: \treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"no pod found for sandbox %s\", sandboxName)\n366: }\n367: \n368: func BuildEntryPoints(podIP string, ports []types.TargetPort) []types.SandboxEntryPoint {\n369: \tvar entryPoints []types.SandboxEntryPoint\n370: \n371: \tfor _, port := range ports {\n372: \t\tentryPoint := types.SandboxEntryPoint{\n373: \t\t\tPath:     port.PathPrefix,\n374: \t\t\tProtocol: port.Protocol,\n375: \t\t\tEndpoint: net.JoinHostPort(podIP, fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", port.Port)),\n376: \t\t}\n377: \t\tentryPoints = append(entryPoints, entryPoint)\n378: \t}\n379: \n380: \treturn entryPoints\n381: }\n382: \n383: func (p *SandboxProcessor) CreateSandbox(\n384: \tctx context.Context,\n385: \tsandbox *unstructured.Unstructured,\n386: \tisWarmPool bool,\n387: \tuserClient dynamic.ResourceInterface,\n388: \tsessionID string,\n389: ) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n390: \tsandboxName := sandbox.GetName()\n391: \tsandboxNamespace := sandbox.GetNamespace()\n392: \n393: \tworkloadName := sandboxName\n394: \tif idx := strings.LastIndex(sandboxName, \"-\"); idx > 0 {\n395: \t\tworkloadName = sandboxName[:idx]\n396: \t}\n397: \n398: \tinfo := &types.SandboxInfo{\n399: \t\tSessionID:    sessionID,\n400: \t\tSandboxID:    sandboxName,\n401: \t\tSandboxName:  sandboxName,\n402: \t\tKind:         \"Sandbox\",\n403: \t\tNamespace:    sandboxNamespace,\n404: \t\tWorkloadName: workloadName,\n405: \t\tStatus:       \"pending\",\n406: \t\tCreatedAt:    time.Now(),\n407: \t\tUpdatedAt:    time.Now(),\n408: \t}\n409: \n410: \tif isWarmPool {\n411: \t\tinfo.Kind = \"SandboxClaim\"\n412: \t}\n413: \n414: \tcreateCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, 2*time.Minute)\n415: \tdefer cancel()\n416: \n417: \t_, err := userClient.Create(createCtx, sandbox, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n418: \tif err != nil {\n419: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create sandbox: %w\", err)\n420: \t}\n421: \n422: \trunningChan := make(chan struct{})\n423: \terrChan := make(chan error, 1)\n424: \n425: \tgo func() {\n426: \t\tfor {\n427: \t\t\tselect {\n428: \t\t\tcase <-createCtx.Done():\n429: \t\t\t\terrChan <- ErrSandboxCreationTimeout\n430: \t\t\t\treturn\n431: \t\t\tdefault:\n432: \t\t\t\tpod, err := p.podLister.Pods(sandboxNamespace).Get(sandboxName)\n433: \t\t\t\tif err == nil && pod.Status.Phase == corev1.PodRunning && pod.Status.PodIP != \"\" {\n434: \t\t\t\t\tclose(runningChan)\n435: \t\t\t\t\treturn\n436: \t\t\t\t}\n437: \t\t\t\ttime.Sleep(500 * time.Millisecond)\n438: \t\t\t}\n439: \t\t}\n440: \t}()\n441: \n442: \tselect {\n443: \tcase <-runningChan:\n444: \tcase err := <-errChan:\n445: \t\tp.rollback(ctx, userClient, sandboxName)\n446: \t\treturn nil, err\n447: \tcase <-time.After(2 * time.Minute):\n448: \t\tp.rollback(ctx, userClient, sandboxName)\n449: \t\treturn nil, ErrSandboxCreationTimeout\n450: \t}\n451: \n452: \tpodIP, err := p.resolvePodIP(ctx, sandboxNamespace, sandboxName)\n453: \tif err != nil {\n454: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to resolve pod IP: %w\", err)\n455: \t}\n456: \n457: \tinfo.PodIP = podIP\n458: \n459: \tports := []types.TargetPort{\n460: \t\t{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"},\n461: \t}\n462: \tinfo.EntryPoints = BuildEntryPoints(podIP, ports)\n463: \tinfo.Status = \"running\"\n464: \tinfo.UpdatedAt = time.Now()\n465: \n466: \treturn info, nil\n467: }\n468: \n469: func (p *SandboxProcessor) rollback(ctx context.Context, client dynamic.ResourceInterface, name string) {\n470: \tdeleteCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, 30*time.Second)\n471: \tdefer cancel()\n472: \tclient.Delete(deleteCtx, name, metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n473: }\n\n(End of file - total 473 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package processor\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"crypto/rand\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"math/big\"\n\t\"net\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/unstructured\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/labels\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n\tcorev1lister \"k8s.io/client-go/listers/core/v1\"\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/processor/sandbox_processor.go","time":{"start":1775844112383,"end":1775844112401}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844112405,"sessionID":"ses_28772e49effe617laS4xnvcyTz","part":{"id":"prt_d788eb225001m4U4D2igDqBKyi","messageID":"msg_d788de8990015OAgdLtehtCT7J","sessionID":"ses_28772e49effe617laS4xnvcyTz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2484e641641749fe98a52e97","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `CreateSandboxRequest` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n18:   - Fields: `Kind`, `Name`, `Namespace` (all string)\n19:   - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n20:   - Validation rules: Kind ∈ {AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter}, Namespace non-empty, Name non-empty\n21: \n22: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `CreateSandboxResponse` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n23:   - Fields: `SessionID`, `SandboxID`, `SandboxName` (string), `EntryPoints` ([]SandboxEntryPoint)\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `SandboxEntryPoint` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n26:   - Fields: `Path`, `Protocol`, `Endpoint` (all string)\n27: \n28: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define context keys in `pkg/workloadmanager/auth.go`\n29:   - Keys: `contextKeyUserToken`, `contextKeyServiceAccount`, `contextKeyServiceAccountName`, `contextKeyNamespace`\n30: \n31: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Define constants in `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n32:   - Constants: `DefaultSandboxTTL` (8h), `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` (15m), label/annotation keys\n33: \n34: ### Phase 2: Infrastructure Components\n35: \n36: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `sandboxCreator` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/sandbox_creator.go`\n37:   - Fields: `k8sClient`, `sandboxController`, `storeClient`, `publicKey`\n38: \n39: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `createSandbox()` method for `sandboxCreator`\n40:   - Steps: register watcher → store placeholder → create CR → wait (2min) → resolve IP → update store\n41:   - Rollback on failure: delete CR + delete store entry\n42:   - Use independent 30s timeout context for rollback delete\n43: \n44: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `resolvePodIP()` method in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n45:   - Priority: sandbox name → annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` → informer cache → label selector\n46:   - Require PodRunning phase and non-empty PodIP\n47: \n48: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `buildEntryPoints()` function in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n49:   - Input: podIP, []TargetPort\n50:   - Output: []SandboxEntryPoint with format `host:port`\n51: \n52: ### Phase 3: Workload Builders\n53: \n54: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `buildSandboxObject()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n55:   - Input: *AgentRuntime, sessionID\n56:   - Name format: `{workloadName}-{RandString(8)}`\n57:   - Set labels: session-id, workload-name, sandbox-name, managed-by\n58:   - Set annotations: idle-timeout\n59:   - Copy podTemplate from runtime.Spec.Template\n60:   - Set replicas=1, lifecycle.shutdownTime=now+MaxSessionDuration\n61: \n62: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `buildSandboxClaimObject()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/workload_builder.go`\n63:   - For CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize > 0\n64:   - Minimal metadata, no full PodSpec\n65:   - APIVersion: `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, Kind: `SandboxClaim`\n66: \n67: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement AuthMode injection for CodeInterpreter\n68:   - If AuthMode=picod and publicKey available: inject `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var\n69:   - Support optional fields: Command, Args, Environment, Resources, RuntimeClassName, ImagePullPolicy, ImagePullSecrets\n70: \n71: ### Phase 4: HTTP Handlers\n72: \n73: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `handleAgentRuntimeCreate()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/agent_runtime.go`\n74:   - Parse JSON → set Kind=AgentRuntime → Validate()\n75:   - Get AgentRuntime from informer lister\n76:   - Check podTemplate non-nil\n77:   - Call createSandbox()\n78:   - Return CreateSandboxResponse (200) or error\n79: \n80: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `handleCodeInterpreterCreate()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/code_interpreter.go`\n81:   - Similar to AgentRuntime but:\n82:   - Kind=CodeInterpreter\n83:   - Support WarmPoolSize > 0 → buildSandboxClaimObject()\n84:   - Support AuthMode (picod/none)\n85:   - Default ports: [{Port: 8080, Protocol: \"HTTP\", PathPrefix: \"/\"}] if spec.Ports empty\n86: \n87: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Register routes in `pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go`\n88:   - POST /v1/agent-runtime → handleAgentRuntimeCreate\n89:   - DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId → handleDeleteSandbox\n90:   - POST /v1/code-interpreter → handleCodeInterpreterCreate\n91:   - DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/:sessionId → handleDeleteSandbox\n92: \n93: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `handleDeleteSandbox()` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/agent_runtime.go`\n94:   - Load session from store by sessionId\n95:   - NotFound → 404 with message `Session ID <id> not found, maybe already deleted`\n96:   - Delete SandboxClaim if Kind=SandboxClaim, else delete Sandbox\n97:   - API NotFound on delete → treat as success\n98:   - DeleteSandboxBySessionID from store\n99:   - Return 200 `{\"message\":\"Sandbox deleted successfully\"}`\n100: \n101: ### Phase 5: Error Handling\n102: \n103: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Define error constants in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go` or `pkg/workloadmanager/response/response.go`\n104:   - ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound, ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound, ErrTemplateMissing, ErrPublicKeyMissing\n105: \n106: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement error mapping in handlers\n107:   - JSON bind失败 → 400 `Invalid request body`\n108:   - Validate 失败 → 400 `<field> is required`\n109:   - Template missing → 400 with `pod template` in message\n110:   - NotFound from informer → 404 `agent runtime not found` / `code interpreter not found`\n111:   - Auth失败 → 401 from authMiddleware\n112:   - Timeout/internal → 500 `internal server error`\n113: \n114: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement rollback strategy in `createSandbox()`\n115:   - CR 创建前失败: delete store placeholder\n116:   - CR 创建后超时: delete CR (30s timeout) + delete store\n117:   - Pod IP 解析失败: delete CR + delete store\n118:   - Store 更新失败: log warning, CR left for GC\n119: \n120: ### Phase 6: Integration\n121: \n122: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Integrate with `client-go` typed clients\n123:   - Use `AgentRuntimeInterface` and `CodeInterpreterInterface` for reading templates\n124:   - Use informers + listers for cached reads\n125: \n126: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Integrate with dynamic client\n127:   - Create Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs using `dynamic.Interface`\n128:   - GVR: `SandboxGVR`, `SandboxClaimGVR`\n129: \n130: - [ ] **TASK-052**: Integrate with SandboxReconciler\n131:   - Call `WatchSandboxOnce(ns, name)` before CR creation\n132:   - Wait on channel with 2min timeout\n133:   - Receive notification when status=running\n134: \n135: - [ ] **TASK-053**: Integrate with Store\n136:   - StoreSandbox() with placeholder before CR create\n137:   - UpdateSandbox() with full info after IP resolution\n138:   - DeleteSandboxBySessionID() on rollback or delete\n139: \n140: - [ ] **TASK-054**: Integrate with authMiddleware\n141:   - When EnableAuth=true: use per-user dynamic client from `GetOrCreateUserK8sClient`\n142:   - Cache key: `<namespace>:<serviceAccountName>`\n143: \n144: ### Phase 7: Testing (TDD)\n145: \n146: #### Unit Tests\n147: \n148: - [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestCreateSandboxRequest_Validate` in `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers_test.go`\n149:   - Valid request → no error\n150:   - Empty name → error contains `name is required`\n151:   - Empty namespace → error contains `namespace is required`\n152:   - Invalid kind → error contains `kind is required`\n153: \n154: - [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_Success` (TestCase-WM-001)\n155:   - Given: valid AgentRuntime in informer cache\n156:   - When: POST /v1/agent-runtime with valid JSON\n157:   - Then: 200, response contains sessionId and entryPoints\n158:   - Use fake clientset + mock store + mock SandboxReconciler\n159: \n160: - [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_Idempotent` (TestCase-WM-002)\n161:   - Given: two consecutive requests with same name\n162:   - When: first creation succeeds\n163:   - Then: second returns same sessionId\n164: \n165: - [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestHandleAgentRuntimeCreate_MissingPodTemplate` (TestCase-WM-003)\n166:   - Given: AgentRuntime with spec.podTemplate=nil\n167:   - When: POST /v1/agent-runtime\n168:   - Then: 400, message contains `pod template`\n169: \n170: - [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_WarmPool`\n171:   - Given: CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize > 0\n172:   - When: POST /v1/code-interpreter\n173:   - Then: creates SandboxClaim, response Kind=SandboxClaim\n174: \n175: - [ ] **TEST-006**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_DefaultPorts`\n176:   - Given: CodeInterpreter with empty spec.Ports\n177:   - When: creation succeeds\n178:   - Then: entryPoints contains default 8080/HTTP\n179: \n180: - [ ] **TEST-007**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_AuthModePicoD`\n181:   - Given: AuthMode=picod and publicKey available\n182:   - When: sandbox created\n183:   - Then: PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY env var injected\n184: \n185: - [ ] **TEST-008**: `TestHandleCodeInterpreterCreate_AuthModeNone`\n186:   - Given: AuthMode=none\n187:   - When: sandbox created\n188:   - Then: no PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY env var\n189: \n190: - [ ] **TEST-009**: `TestCreateSandbox_Timeout`\n191:   - Given: no running notification within 2min\n192:   - When: createSandbox() waits\n193:   - Then: error `sandbox creation timed out`, CR deleted, store entry deleted\n194: \n195: - [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestCreateSandbox_RollbackOnIPResolutionFailure`\n196:   - Given: pod IP resolution fails\n197:   - When: createSandbox() attempts to resolve\n198:   - Then: CR deleted, store entry deleted, error returned\n199: \n200: - [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestResolvePodIP_FromAnnotation`\n201:   - Given: Sandbox with annotation `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name`\n202:   - When: resolvePodIP() called\n203:   - Then: uses annotated pod name\n204: \n205: - [ ] **TEST-012**: `TestResolvePodIP_FromOwnerReference`\n206:   - Given: pods listed by label, one has owner reference Kind=Sandbox\n207:   - When: resolvePodIP() called\n208:   - Then: selects pod with matching owner reference\n209: \n210: - [ ] **TEST-013**: `TestResolvePodIP_PodNotRunning`\n211:   - Given: pod in Pending/Failed phase\n212:   - When: resolvePodIP() called\n213:   - Then: error indicating pod not running\n214: \n215: - [ ] **TEST-014**: `TestBuildSandboxObject_LabelsAndAnnotations`\n216:   - Given: AgentRuntime with sessionTimeout\n217:   - When: buildSandboxObject() called\n218:   - Then: labels and annotations set correctly\n219: \n220: - [ ] **TEST-015**: `TestBuildSandboxClaimObject_MinimalMetadata`\n221:   - Given: CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize > 0\n222:   - When: buildSandboxClaimObject() called\n223:   - Then: minimal metadata, no PodSpec\n224: \n225: - [ ] **TEST-016**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_Success`\n226:   - Given: session exists in store\n227:   - When: DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId\n228:   - Then: 200, CR deleted, store entry deleted\n229: \n230: - [ ] **TEST-017**: `TestHandleDeleteSandbox_NotFound` (Spec requirement)\n231:   - Given: no session key in store\n232:   - When: DELETE invoked\n233:   - Then: 404, message contains session id\n234: \n235: #### Test Infrastructure\n236: \n237: - [ ] **TEST-020**: Create `testEnv` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/server_test.go`\n238:   - Fields: k8sClient, reconciler, store, server, redis (miniredis), fakeClient, dynamicClient\n239: \n240: - [ ] **TEST-021**: Implement `newTestEnv(t *testing.T)` function\n241:   - Start miniredis\n242:   - Create fake clientset with registered AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter\n243:   - Create fake dynamic client\n244:   - Initialize K8sClient, SandboxReconciler, Store\n245:   - Build Server (auth/TLS disabled)\n246: \n247: - [ ] **TEST-022**: Create mock implementations\n248:   - MockWorkloadManager interface\n249:   - Mock SandboxReconciler.WatchSandboxOnce returning controllable channel\n250: \n251: #### Integration Tests\n252: \n253: - [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestE2E_CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox`\n254:   - Deploy AgentCube (Helm install to Kind cluster)\n255:   - Create ServiceAccount and get token\n256:   - POST /v1/agent-runtime\n257:   - Verify response contains sessionId and entryPoints\n258:   - Access sandbox via entryPoint to verify connectivity\n259:   - DELETE /v1/agent-runtime/sessions/:sessionId to cleanup\n260: \n261: - [ ] **TEST-031**: E2E fixture `echo_agent.yaml`\n262:   - Simple echo server AgentRuntime definition\n263: \n264: #### Coverage Verification\n265: \n266: - [ ] **TEST-040**: Run coverage check\n267:   - Command: `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n268:   - Verify test code / business code ratio > 0.4\n269:   - Verify each .go file has corresponding _test.go\n270: \n271: ### Phase 8: Documentation\n272: \n273: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Add API examples to handler doc comments\n274:   - Example request/response for POST /v1/agent-runtime\n275:   - Example request/response for POST /v1/code-interpreter\n276: \n277: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Document error scenarios in handler doc comments\n278:   - List all HTTP status codes and conditions\n279: \n280: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Update pkg/workloadmanager/README.md\n281:   - Architecture diagram\n282:   - Component interaction flow\n283:   - Configuration options\n284: \n285: ## Acceptance Criteria\n286: \n287: - [ ] All handlers implemented and registered\n288: - [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n289: - [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.4\n290: - [ ] Error handling covers all spec-defined scenarios\n291: - [ ] Rollback strategy verified by tests\n292: - [ ] Integration with client-go, informers, dynamic client, Store, SandboxReconciler complete\n293: - [ ] Auth mode (EnableAuth) tested with per-user client cache\n294: - [ ] WarmPool support for CodeInterpreter verified\n295: - [ ] Timeout (2min) and rollback (30s) enforced\n296: - [ ] Pod IP resolution covers all paths (annotation, owner reference, label selector)\n297: \n298: ## Dependencies\n299: \n300: - **Completed**: ST-1 (CRD schemas), ST-2 (HTTP framework, auth middleware, informers)\n301: - **Required**: client-go typed clients, informers, listers operational\n302: - **Required**: SandboxReconciler operational (from controller package)\n303: - **Required**: Store interface (Redis-backed) operational\n\n(End of file - total 303 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `CreateSandboxRequest` struct in `pkg/common/types.go`\n  - Fields: `Kind`, `Name`, `Namespace` (all string)\n  - Method: `Validate()` returning error\n  - Validation rules: Kind ∈ {AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter}, Namespace non-empty, Name non-empty","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/sandbox-orchestration/AR-005-sandbox-creation-processor/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775844112385,"end":1775844112403}}}}
